    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Global Hot Flashes</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Polly Huntington letter on Dec 13 article about apparel for women experiencing hot flashes provides humorous reference to global warming</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Women Dress for Comfort in the Heat of the Night'' (Dec. 13) notes that by 2030, ''according to the World Health Organization, as many as 1.2 billion women worldwide will have reached the age of 50, when hot flashes often occur.'' May one infer that hot flashes will become a factor in global warming?</p>
        <p>Polly Huntington  Farmington, Conn.</p>
      </block>
